{"type":"message","id":"169ee696","parentId":"2039446f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:28.526Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_flmw7zc4rzb7_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose, { Schema, Document, Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport interface ICourseFeeStage {\n  name: string;\n  amount: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ICourse extends Document {\n  license_category_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  code: string; // Mã nội bộ của trung tâm\n  name: string; // Tên khóa học\n  system_course_id?: number;\n  system_course_code?: string; // Mã báo cáo lên Sở GTVT\n  curriculum_id?: number;\n  management_record_number?: string;\n  description?: string;\n  report_start_date?: Date;\n  start_date?: Date;\n  end_date?: Date;\n  dat_date?: Date; // Ngày tập trung chạy DAT\n  cabin_date?: Date; // Ngày học Cabin\n  decision_to_sign?: string;\n  duration?: number;\n  status: 'draft' | 'ongoing' | 'completed' | 'canceled';\n  course_fee?: number;\n  max_students?: number;\n\n  // Extension for Web Admin\n  internal_note?: string;\n  note?: string;\n  course_type?: string;\n  fee_stages?: ICourseFeeStage[];\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst CourseSchema = new Schema<ICourse>({\n  license_category_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'LicenseCategories', default: null },\n  code: { type: String, required: true, unique: true, index: true },\n  name: { type: String, required: true },\n  system_course_id: { type: Number },\n  system_course_code: { type: String },\n  curriculum_id: { type: Number },\n  management_record_number: { type: String },\n  description: { type: String },\n  report_start_date: { type: Date },\n  start_date: { type: Date },\n  end_date: { type: Date },\n  dat_date: { type: Date },\n  cabin_date: { type: Date },\n  decision_to_sign: { type: String },\n  duration: { type: Number },\n  status: { \n    type: String, \n    enum: ['draft', 'ongoing', 'completed', 'canceled'], \n    default: 'draft' \n  },\n  course_fee: { type: Number, default: 0 },\n  max_students: { type: Number, default: 50 },\n  internal_note: { type: String },\n  note: { type: String },\n  course_type: { type: String, default: 'trực tiếp' },\n  fee_stages: [{\n    name: { type: String },\n    amount: { type: Number, default: 0 }\n  }],\n}, {\n  timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n  versionKey: false,\n  collection: 'courses'\n});\n\nCourseSchema.index({ status: 1 });\nCourseSchema.index({ start_date: -1 });\n\nif (mongoose.models.Courses) {\n  mongoose.deleteModel('Courses');\n}\nexport const CourseModel = mongoose.model<ICourse>('Courses', CourseSchema, 'courses');\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742288519}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6d71964","parentId":"169ee696","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:28.533Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_flmw7zc4rzb7_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose, { Schema, Document, Types } from 'mongoose';\nimport { IUser } from './user.model';\n\nexport interface IStudent extends Document {\n  user_id: Types.ObjectId | IUser; // Can be ID or populated User object\n  card_id?: string | null;\n  profile_created_at?: Date | null;\n  email_verified_at?: Date | null;\n  lead_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  region_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  license_category_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  course_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  balance?: any;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n  is_deleted: boolean;\n  deleted_at: Date | null;\n  // Merged fields from Enrollment for UI/Tests (Source of truth is CourseStudent)\n  status_detail?: string;\n}\n\nconst StudentSchema = new Schema<IStudent>({\n  user_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', required: true, index: true },\n  balance: { \n    type: Schema.Types.Decimal128, \n    default: 0,\n    get: (v: any) => (v ? parseFloat(v.toString()) : 0)\n  },\n  card_id: { type: String, default: null },\n  profile_created_at: { type: Date, default: null },\n  email_verified_at: { type: Date, default: null },\n  lead_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Lead_Infos', default: null },\n  course_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Courses', default: null },\n  license_category_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'LicenseCategories', default: null },\n\n  // Extension\n  region_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Cities', default: null },\n  is_deleted: { type: Boolean, default: false, index: true },\n  deleted_at: { type: Date, default: null },\n\n  // Merged fields for UI/Tests (Primary source is CourseStudent)\n  status_detail: { type: String, default: 'Chờ KSK' },\n}, {\n  timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n  versionKey: false,\n  collection: 'studentinfos'\n});\n\nStudentSchema.index({ region_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nStudentSchema.index({ created_at: -1, is_deleted: 1 });\nStudentSchema.index({ course_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nStudentSchema.index({ license_category_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\n\nif (mongoose.models.StudentInfos) {\n  mongoose.deleteModel('StudentInfos');\n}\nexport const StudentModel = mongoose.model<IStudent>('StudentInfos', StudentSchema, 'studentinfos');\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742288526}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f4ff85c","parentId":"b6d71964","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:34.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me also check the user model and how courses relate to teachers. I need to understand:\n1. How users are identified (teacher vs admin)\n2. How courses are linked to teachers\n3. How payments/exams/etc are linked to teachers","thinkingSignature":"62fe87f268baf1a6abbb1357fd5a9e3d9aa0b0d1e59221032dc0bc2a4bc238c9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9vjv9vgpo2bc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/user.model.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9vjv9vgpo2bc_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/lesson.model.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1406,"output":143,"cacheRead":65472,"cacheWrite":1065,"totalTokens":68086,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776742288538,"responseId":"063622912bc0a8acfa3753c9759ecde8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6db8dbe6","parentId":"8f4ff85c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:34.312Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9vjv9vgpo2bc_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose, { Schema, Document } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport enum UserGender {\n  Male = 'male',\n  Female = 'female',\n  Another = 'another',\n}\n\nexport enum UserStatus {\n  Active = 'active',\n  InActive = 'inactive',\n  Deleted = 'deleted',\n}\n\nexport enum UserRole {\n  Admin = 'admin',\n  Staff = 'staff',\n  Teacher = 'teacher',\n  Student = 'student',\n}\n\nexport interface IUser extends Document {\n  username: string;\n  first_name: string;\n  last_name: string;\n  email: string;\n  phone: string;\n  image?: string;\n  bio?: string;\n  gender: UserGender;\n  dob?: Date;\n  address: string;\n  identity_card: string;\n  status: UserStatus;\n  // NOTE: 'role' is removed — use UserRoleModel (userroles collection) instead\n  password: string;\n  refresh_token?: string;\n  existing_license_num?: string;\n  existing_license_rank?: string;\n  zalo_user_id?: string;\n  fcm_token?: string;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst UserSchema = new Schema<IUser>({\n  username: { type: String, required: true, unique: true, lowercase: true, trim: true },\n  first_name: { type: String, required: true },\n  last_name: { type: String, required: true },\n  email: { type: String, required: true, unique: true, lowercase: true, trim: true },\n  phone: { type: String, required: true },\n  image: { type: String },\n  bio: { type: String },\n  gender: { type: String, enum: Object.values(UserGender), default: UserGender.Male },\n  dob: { type: Date },\n  address: { type: String, required: true },\n  identity_card: { \n    type: String, \n    required: true,\n    validate: {\n      validator: function(v: string) {\n        return /^\\d{12}$/.test(v);\n      },\n      message: (props: any) => `${props.value} không phải là số CCCD hợp lệ (phải có đúng 12 chữ số)!`\n    }\n  },\n  status: { type: String, enum: Object.values(UserStatus), default: UserStatus.Active },\n  password: { type: String, required: true },\n  refresh_token: { type: String },\n  existing_license_num: { type: String, default: null },\n  existing_license_rank: { type: String, default: null },\n  zalo_user_id: { type: String, default: null },\n  fcm_token: { type: String, default: null }\n}, {\n  timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n  versionKey: false\n});\n\nUserSchema.index({ \n  first_name: 'text', \n  last_name: 'text', \n  phone: 'text', \n  identity_card: 'text' \n}, { \n  name: 'SearchIndex',\n  weights: { first_name: 10, last_name: 5, phone: 5, identity_card: 3 }\n});\nUserSchema.index({ phone: 1 });\nUserSchema.index({ identity_card: 1 });\nUserSchema.index({ created_at: -1 });\n\nexport const UserModel = mongoose.models.Users || mongoose.model<IUser>('Users', UserSchema);\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742294306}}
{"type":"message","id":"03fa5c96","parentId":"6db8dbe6","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:34.319Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9vjv9vgpo2bc_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose, { Schema, Document, Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport enum LessonStatus {\n  Pending = 'pending',\n  InProgress = 'in_progress',\n  Completed = 'completed',\n  NoTeacher = 'no_teacher',\n  CanceledClass = 'canceled_class',\n  DroppedClass = 'dropped_class',\n  Deleted = 'deleted',\n}\n\nexport enum LessonCategory {\n  Theory = 'theory',\n  Practice = 'practice',\n}\n\nexport interface ILesson extends Document {\n  course_student_id?: Types.ObjectId;\n  student_id?: Types.ObjectId; // References User(student)\n  teacher_id?: Types.ObjectId; // References User(teacher)\n  name: string;\n  category: LessonCategory;\n  status: LessonStatus;\n  start_time: Date;\n  end_time: Date;\n  description?: string;\n  lesson_type_id?: Types.ObjectId;\n  vehicle_id?: Types.ObjectId;\n  is_night_course: boolean;\n  is_automatic_course: boolean;\n  km: number;\n  hour: string;\n  vehicle_type?: string;\n  stadium_id?: Types.ObjectId;\n  order: number;\n  confirmed: boolean;\n  pickup_point?: string;\n  is_pickup: boolean;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst LessonSchema = new Schema<ILesson>({\n  course_student_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'CourseStudents', index: true },\n  student_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', index: true },\n  teacher_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', index: true },\n  name: { type: String, required: true },\n  category: { \n    type: String, \n    enum: Object.values(LessonCategory), \n    default: LessonCategory.Practice,\n    required: true \n  },\n  status: { \n    type: String, \n    enum: Object.values(LessonStatus), \n    default: LessonStatus.Pending,\n    required: true \n  },\n  start_time: { type: Date, required: true, index: true },\n  end_time: { type: Date, required: true },\n  description: { type: String, default: '' },\n  lesson_type_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId },\n  vehicle_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId },\n  is_night_course: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n  is_automatic_course: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n  km: { type: Number, default: 0 },\n  hour: { type: String, default: '00:00' },\n  vehicle_type: { type: String, enum: ['car', 'motorbike'] },\n  stadium_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Stadiums' },\n  order: { type: Number, default: 1 },\n  confirmed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n  pickup_point: { type: String },\n  is_pickup: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n}, {\n  timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n  versionKey: false\n});\n\nexport const LessonModel = mongoose.models.Lessons || mongoose.model<ILesson>('Lessons', LessonSchema);\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742294313}}
{"type":"message","id":"037c047c","parentId":"03fa5c96","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:39.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me check some key controllers to understand how they query data currently.","thinkingSignature":"f01a911175566382100a369bd68776bf1ba3fec91b48c29dc5532e1561334ed2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0rr1upouphm4_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/course.controller.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0rr1upouphm4_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/student.controller.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1504,"output":106,"cacheRead":66348,"cacheWrite":1676,"totalTokens":69634,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776742294322,"responseId":"0636229766252d9aa711fb473ef078d0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a171458","parentId":"037c047c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:39.960Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0rr1upouphm4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type {} from '../types/express.d';\nimport { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { CourseService } from '@/application/services/course.service';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\nimport { ctrlLogger } from '@/infrastructure/logging/controller-logger';\n\nconst courseService = new CourseService();\n\nexport const getAllCourses = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.get_all', req);\n  log.start({ query: req.query });\n\n  const courses = await courseService.getAllCourses(req.query, req.pagination);\n  log.success(res, courses, 'Courses retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getCourseById = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.get_by_id', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  log.start({ courseId: idStr });\n\n  const course = await courseService.getCourseById(idStr);\n  log.success(res, course, 'Course retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const createCourse = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.create', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const course = await courseService.createCourse(req.body);\n  log.success(res, course, 'Course created successfully');\n});\n\nexport const updateCourse = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.update', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  log.start({ courseId: idStr });\n\n  const course = await courseService.updateCourse(idStr, req.body);\n  log.success(res, course, 'Course updated successfully');\n});\n\nexport const deleteCourse = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.delete', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  log.start({ courseId: idStr });\n\n  await courseService.deleteCourse(idStr);\n  log.success(res, null, 'Course deleted successfully');\n});\n\nexport const exportCourses = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.export', req);\n  log.start({ query: req.query });\n\n  await courseService.exportCoursesToExcel(res, req.query);\n  // Export streams response directly; no success log needed (response already sent)\n});\n\nexport const getUnassignedStudents = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.get_unassigned', req);\n  log.start({ query: req.query });\n\n  const result = await courseService.getUnassignedStudents(req.query, req.pagination);\n  log.success(res, result, 'Unassigned students retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const assignStudents = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.assign_students', req);\n  const { id } = req.params as { id: string };\n  const { studentIds } = req.body;\n  log.start({ courseId: id, studentCount: Array.isArray(studentIds) ? studentIds.length : 0 });\n\n  const result = await courseService.assignStudentsToCourse(id, studentIds);\n  log.success(res, result, 'Students assigned to course successfully');\n});\nexport const getStats = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.get_stats', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const stats = await courseService.getCourseStats();\n  log.success(res, stats, 'Course statistics retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const importFromExcel = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.import_excel', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  if (!req.file) {\n    throw new Error('No Excel file uploaded');\n  }\n\n  if (!req.user) {\n    throw new Error('User not authenticated');\n  }\n\n  const result = await courseService.importCoursesFromExcel(\n    req.file.path,\n    req.user.id,\n    req.user.role || 'admin'\n  );\n\n  log.success(res, result, 'Course import started in the background');\n});\n\nexport const getTemplate = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('course.get_template', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  await courseService.getCourseImportTemplate(res);\n  // Result streamed directly to response\n});\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742299954}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a062c46","parentId":"8a171458","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:39.966Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0rr1upouphm4_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type {} from '../types/express.d';\nimport { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { StudentService } from '@/application/services/student.service';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\nimport { LICENSE_CATEGORIES } from '@/domain/constants/student.constants';\nimport { LicenseCategoryModel } from '@/infrastructure/database/models/license_category.model';\nimport { ctrlLogger } from '@/infrastructure/logging/controller-logger';\nimport { ExcelHelper } from '@/infrastructure/utils/excel.helper';\n\n// Initialize the service cleanly\nconst studentService = new StudentService();\n\nexport const createStudent = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.create', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const student = await studentService.createStudent(req.body);\n  console.log('[DEBUG] createStudent payload:', JSON.stringify(req.body, null, 2));\n  log.success((res as any), student, 'Student created successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getAllStudents = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.get_all', req);\n  log.start({ query: req.query });\n\n  const filters = { ...req.query };\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    filters.teacher_id = req.user.id;\n  }\n\n  const pagination = req.pagination || { page: 1, limit: 10 };\n  const students = await studentService.getAllStudents(filters, pagination);\n  log.success(res, students, 'Students retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getStudentById = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.get_by_id', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : (req.params.id as string[])[0];\n  log.start({ studentId: idStr });\n\n  const student = await studentService.getStudentById(idStr);\n  \n  // Data Isolation Check for Teachers\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    const isAssigned = await studentService.isStudentAssignedToTeacher(idStr, req.user.id);\n    if (!isAssigned) {\n      return log.fail('access_denied', res, 403, 'Bạn không có quyền truy cập học viên này');\n    }\n  }\n\n  log.success(res, student, 'Student retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const updateStudent = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.update', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : (req.params.id as string[])[0];\n  log.start({ studentId: idStr });\n\n  // Data Isolation Check for Teachers\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    const isAssigned = await studentService.isStudentAssignedToTeacher(idStr, req.user.id);\n    if (!isAssigned) {\n      return log.fail('access_denied', res, 403, 'Bạn không có quyền chỉnh sửa học viên này');\n    }\n  }\n\n  const updated = await studentService.updateStudent(idStr, req.body);\n  log.success(res, updated, 'Student updated successfully');\n});\n\nexport const deleteStudent = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.delete', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : (req.params.id as string[])[0];\n  log.start({ studentId: idStr });\n\n  // Data Isolation Check for Teachers\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    const isAssigned = await studentService.isStudentAssignedToTeacher(idStr, req.user.id);\n    if (!isAssigned) {\n      return log.fail('access_denied', res, 403, 'Bạn không có quyền xóa học viên này');\n    }\n  }\n\n  const deleted = await studentService.deleteStudent(idStr);\n  log.success(res, deleted, 'Student deleted successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getStudentHistory = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.history', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : (req.params.id as string[])[0];\n  log.start({ studentId: idStr });\n\n  const pagination = (req as any).pagination || { page: 1, limit: 20 };\n  const history = await studentService.getStudentHistory(idStr, pagination);\n  log.success((res as any), history, 'Student history retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getLicenseCategories = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.license_categories', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const categories = await LicenseCategoryModel.find({}).sort({ name: 1 }).exec();\n  log.success((res as any), categories, 'License categories retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const exportStudents = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.export', req);\n  \n  const filters = { ...req.query };\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    filters.teacher_id = req.user.id;\n  }\n  \n  log.start({ query: filters });\n\n  await studentService.exportStudentsToExcel(res, filters);\n  // Export streams response directly; no success log needed (response already sent)\n});\n\nexport const importStudents = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.import', req);\n  if (!(req as any).file) {\n    return log.fail('missing_file', res, 400, 'Không tìm thấy file tải lên');\n  }\n\n  log.start({ fileName: (req as any).file.originalname, userId: req.user?.id });\n\n  const courseId = req.body.course_id;\n  const userId = req.user?.id || req.user?._id;\n  const userRole = req.user?.role;\n\n  // Use type assertion to bypass stale TS warnings if any\n  const results = await (studentService as any).importStudentsFromExcel(\n    (req as any).file.path, \n    userId, \n    userRole,\n    courseId\n  );\n\n  log.success((res as any), results, 'Quá trình nhập dữ liệu học viên đã được bắt đầu trong nền');\n});\n\nexport const downloadTemplate = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.download_template', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const excelHelper = new ExcelHelper();\n  await excelHelper.getImportTemplate(res);\n});\n\nexport const getImportStats = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('student.get_import_stats', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const stats = await studentService.getImportManagementStats();\n  log.success((res as any), stats, 'Student import statistics retrieved successfully');\n});\n\n// Trigger recompilation\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742299960}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9f30ac2","parentId":"5a062c46","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:49.027Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding. Let me also check the dashboard and exam controllers, and the user_role model to understand how roles work.","thinkingSignature":"aff0309c35417257edc626b03dc6ae12e3def212229805dbe72e52ea5390b74e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jv6wv9cvea1s_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/user_role.model.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jv6wv9cvea1s_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":2611,"output":120,"cacheRead":67876,"cacheWrite":1696,"totalTokens":72303,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776742299974,"responseId":"0636229df95246c2469eb86e1d88846f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d45534f","parentId":"a9f30ac2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:49.056Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jv6wv9cvea1s_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose, { Schema, Document, Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport interface IUserRole extends Document {\n  user_id: Types.ObjectId;\n  role_id: Types.ObjectId;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst UserRoleSchema = new Schema<IUserRole>(\n  {\n    user_id: {\n      type: Schema.Types.ObjectId,\n      ref: 'Users',\n      required: [true, 'User ID là bắt buộc'],\n      index: true,\n    },\n    role_id: {\n      type: Schema.Types.ObjectId,\n      ref: 'Roles',\n      required: [true, 'Role ID là bắt buộc'],\n    },\n  },\n  {\n    timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n    versionKey: false,\n    collection: 'userroles',\n  },\n);\n\n// Compound unique index: one user can have one role per entry\nUserRoleSchema.index({ user_id: 1, role_id: 1 }, { unique: true });\n\nexport const UserRoleModel = mongoose.models.UserRole || mongoose.model<IUserRole>('UserRole', UserRoleSchema, 'userroles');\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742309049}}
{"type":"message","id":"a26bac8b","parentId":"6d45534f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:49.063Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jv6wv9cvea1s_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type {} from \"../types/express.d\";\nimport { Request, Response } from \"express\";\nimport mongoose from \"mongoose\";\nimport { StudentModel } from \"@/infrastructure/database/models/student.model\";\nimport { CourseStudentModel } from \"@/infrastructure/database/models/course_student.model\";\nimport { NotificationModel } from \"@/infrastructure/database/models/notification.model\";\nimport { ExamScheduleModel } from \"@/infrastructure/database/models/exam_schedule.model\";\nimport { catchAsync } from \"@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware\";\nimport { ctrlLogger } from \"@/infrastructure/logging/controller-logger\";\nimport { ExcelHelper } from \"@/infrastructure/utils/excel.helper\";\nimport { NotifyService } from \"@/application/services/notify.service\";\n\nconst notifyService = new NotifyService();\n\nexport const getDashboardStats = catchAsync(\n  async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const log = ctrlLogger(\"dashboard.get_stats\", req);\n    log.start({ userId: (req.user as any)?.id ?? (req.user as any)?._id });\n    const today = new Date();\n    today.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);\n\n    // --- MONTH BOUNDARIES ---\n    const startOfThisMonth = new Date(today.getFullYear(), today.getMonth(), 1);\n    const startOfLastMonth = new Date(\n      today.getFullYear(),\n      today.getMonth() - 1,\n      1,\n    );\n    const endOfLastMonth = new Date(\n      today.getFullYear(),\n      today.getMonth(),\n      0,\n      23,\n      59,\n      59,\n      999,\n    );\n\n    const sevenDaysLater = new Date(today);\n    sevenDaysLater.setDate(today.getDate() + 7);\n    sevenDaysLater.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999);\n\n    const thirtyDaysLater = new Date(today);\n    thirtyDaysLater.setDate(today.getDate() + 30);\n    thirtyDaysLater.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999);\n\n    const fortyEightHoursLater = new Date();\n    fortyEightHoursLater.setHours(fortyEightHoursLater.getHours() + 48);\n\n    // --- DATA ISOLATION ---\n    const studentMatch: any = { is_deleted: false };\n    const enrollmentMatch: any = {};\n    const userId = (req.user as any)?.id || (req.user as any)?._id;\n\n    if (req.user?.role === \"teacher\") {\n      const assignedStudentIds = await CourseStudentModel.find({\n        teacher_id: userId,\n      })\n        .distinct(\"student_id\")\n        .exec();\n      studentMatch._id = { $in: assignedStudentIds };\n      enrollmentMatch.teacher_id = new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(userId);\n    }\n\n    // 1. Core counts (Filtered by teacher if necessary)\n    const [totalStudents, thisMonthCount, lastMonthCount] = await Promise.all([\n      StudentModel.countDocuments(studentMatch),\n      StudentModel.countDocuments({\n        ...studentMatch,\n        created_at: { $gte: startOfThisMonth },\n      }),\n      StudentModel.countDocuments({\n        ...studentMatch,\n        created_at: { $gte: startOfLastMonth, $lte: endOfLastMonth },\n      }),\n    ]);\n\n    // 2. Monthly growth %\n    const monthlyGrowthPercent =\n      lastMonthCount > 0\n        ? Math.round(((thisMonthCount - lastMonthCount) / lastMonthCount) * 100)\n        : thisMonthCount > 0\n          ? 100\n          : 0;\n\n    // 3. Status distribution (Aggregating from StudentModel for consistency with list)\n    const statusCounts = await StudentModel.aggregate([\n      { $match: studentMatch },\n      {\n        $group: {\n          _id: { $ifNull: [\"$status_detail\", \"Chờ KSK\"] },\n          count: { $sum: 1 },\n        },\n      },\n    ]);\n\n    // 4. Total tuition debt\n    const debtAgg = await CourseStudentModel.aggregate([\n      { $match: { ...enrollmentMatch, $expr: { $lt: [\"$paid_fee\", \"$fee\"] } } },\n      {\n        $group: {\n          _id: null,\n          totalDebt: { $sum: { $subtract: [\"$fee\", \"$paid_fee\"] } },\n          count: { $sum: 1 },\n        },\n      },\n    ]);\n    const totalDebtAmount = debtAgg[0]?.totalDebt ?? 0;\n    const tuitionDebtCount = debtAgg[0]?.count ?? 0;\n\n    // 5. Weekly exam count\n    const weeklyExamCount = await ExamScheduleModel.countDocuments({\n      start_time: { $gte: today, $lte: sevenDaysLater },\n    });\n\n    // 6. Upcoming exams (30 days) - Robust query and formatting\n    const rawUpcoming = await ExamScheduleModel.find({\n      start_time: { $gte: today, $lte: thirtyDaysLater },\n    })\n      .sort({ start_time: 1 })\n      .limit(5)\n      .populate({\n        path: \"exam_id\",\n        select: \"name exam_type license_category_id\",\n        populate: { path: \"license_category_id\", select: \"name\" },\n      })\n      .lean();\n\n    const upcomingExams = rawUpcoming.map((e: any) => {\n      const exam = e.exam_id as any;\n      // Handle cases where exam_id might be a dangling reference (deleted exam)\n      return {\n        ...e,\n        exam_id: {\n          _id: exam?._id || e.exam_id || \"deleted\",\n          name: exam?.name || \"Kỳ thi không tên (Đã xóa)\",\n          exam_type: exam?.exam_type || \"sat_hach\",\n          license_category_id: exam?.license_category_id?.name || \"B2\",\n        },\n      };\n    });\n\n    // 7. Latest registrations (Student Profiles)\n    const rawLatest = await StudentModel.find(studentMatch)\n      .sort({ created_at: -1 })\n      .limit(5)\n      .populate(\"user_id\", \"first_name last_name phone email identity_card\")\n      .populate(\"license_category_id\", \"name\")\n      .populate(\"region_id\", \"name\")\n      .lean();\n\n    const latestRegistrations = await Promise.all(\n      rawLatest.map(async (st: any) => {\n        const user = st.user_id as any;\n        const region = st.region_id as any;\n\n        // Check if truly enrolled (existence in CourseStudent) if fields are missing on profile\n        let courseId = st.course_id;\n        let rankId = st.license_category_id as any;\n\n        if (!courseId || !rankId) {\n          const enrollment = await CourseStudentModel.findOne({\n            student_id: st._id,\n          })\n            .populate(\"license_category_id\", \"name\")\n            .lean();\n\n          if (enrollment) {\n            if (!courseId) courseId = enrollment.course_id;\n            if (!rankId) rankId = enrollment.license_category_id;\n          }\n        }\n\n        return {\n          ...st,\n          id: st._id.toString(),\n          user_id: user,\n          region_id: region,\n          status_detail: st.status_detail || \"Chờ KSK\",\n          license_category_id:\n            rankId?.name ||\n            (st.license_category_id as any)?.name ||\n            \"Chưa phân hạng\",\n          course_id: courseId || null,\n          region: region ? region.name : \"Chưa xác định\",\n        };\n      }),\n    );\n\n    // 8. Region distribution (from StudentModel for global reach analysis)\n    const regionStats = await StudentModel.aggregate([\n      { $match: studentMatch },\n      {\n        $lookup: {\n          from: \"cities\",\n          localField: \"region_id\",\n          foreignField: \"_id\",\n          as: \"region\",\n        },\n      },\n      { $unwind: { path: \"$region\", preserveNullAndEmptyArrays: true } },\n      {\n        $group: {\n          _id: { $ifNull: [\"$region.name\", \"Chưa xác định\"] },\n          count: { $sum: 1 },\n        },\n      },\n      { $sort: { count: -1 } },\n    ]);\n\n    // 9. Recruiter (Sale) distribution\n    const recruiterStats = await CourseStudentModel.aggregate([\n      { $match: enrollmentMatch },\n      {\n        $lookup: {\n          from: \"users\",\n          localField: \"sale_id\",\n          foreignField: \"_id\",\n          as: \"recruiter\",\n        },\n      },\n      { $unwind: { path: \"$recruiter\", preserveNullAndEmptyArrays: true } },\n      {\n        $group: {\n          _id: {\n            $cond: [\n              { $not: [\"$sale_id\"] },\n              \"Chưa gán\",\n              {\n                $ifNull: [\n                  {\n                    $concat: [\n                      \"$recruiter.last_name\",\n                      \" \",\n                      \"$recruiter.first_name\",\n                    ],\n                  },\n                  \"Chưa gán\",\n                ],\n              },\n            ],\n          },\n          count: { $sum: 1 },\n        },\n      },\n      { $sort: { count: -1 } },\n    ]);\n\n    // 10. === URGENT TASKS GENERATOR ===\n    const urgentTasks: Array<{\n      type: \"debt\" | \"exam\" | \"dat\";\n      title: string;\n      subTitle: string;\n      value?: string;\n      badge?: string;\n    }> = [];\n\n    // Top debt enrollments\n    const debtStudents = await CourseStudentModel.find({\n      ...enrollmentMatch,\n      $expr: { $lt: [\"$paid_fee\", \"$fee\"] },\n    })\n      .sort({ paid_fee: 1 })\n      .limit(2)\n      .populate({\n        path: \"student_id\",\n        populate: { path: \"user_id\", select: \"first_name last_name\" },\n      });\n\n    for (const cs of debtStudents) {\n      const st = cs.student_id as any;\n      const u = st?.user_id;\n      const debtAmount = (cs.fee ?? 0) - (cs.paid_fee ?? 0);\n      urgentTasks.push({\n        type: \"debt\",\n        title: u ? `${u.last_name} ${u.first_name}` : \"Học viên ẩn\",\n        subTitle: \"Hạn đóng học phí chưa thanh toán\",\n        value: `-${debtAmount.toLocaleString(\"vi-VN\")} đ`,\n      });\n    }\n\n    // Exams within 48h\n    const urgentExams = await ExamScheduleModel.find({\n      start_time: { $gte: new Date(), $lte: fortyEightHoursLater },\n    })\n      .sort({ start_time: 1 })\n      .limit(2)\n      .populate({\n        path: \"exam_id\",\n        select: \"name license_category_id\",\n        populate: { path: \"license_category_id\", select: \"name\" },\n      });\n\n    for (const e of urgentExams) {\n      const exam = e.exam_id as { name: string; license_category_id: string };\n      const startDate = new Date(e.start_time);\n      const dayLabel = startDate.toLocaleDateString(\"vi-VN\", {\n        weekday: \"long\",\n        hour: \"2-digit\",\n        minute: \"2-digit\",\n      });\n      urgentTasks.push({\n        type: \"exam\",\n        title: exam?.name ?? \"Kỳ thi sắp diễn ra\",\n        subTitle: `Khai mạc: ${dayLabel}`,\n        badge: (exam?.license_category_id as any)?.name ?? \"B2\",\n      });\n    }\n\n    // Enrollments with incomplete DAT\n    const datPendingStudents = await CourseStudentModel.find({\n      ...enrollmentMatch,\n      \"progress_flags.dat_completed\": false,\n      status_detail: { $in: [\"Đang học\", \"Chờ thi\"] },\n    })\n      .limit(2)\n      .populate({\n        path: \"student_id\",\n        populate: { path: \"user_id\", select: \"first_name last_name\" },\n      })\n      .populate({\n        path: \"course_id\",\n        populate: { path: \"license_category_id\", select: \"name\" },\n      });\n\n    for (const cs of datPendingStudents) {\n      const st = cs.student_id as any;\n      const u = st?.user_id;\n      const course = cs.course_id as any;\n      urgentTasks.push({\n        type: \"dat\",\n        title: u ? `${u.last_name} ${u.first_name}` : \"Học viên ẩn\",\n        subTitle: \"Chưa hoàn thành số giờ lái DAT\",\n        badge: course?.license_category_id?.name ?? \"B2\",\n      });\n    }\n\n    // --- Format status counts ---\n    const countsMap: Record<string, number> = {\n      total: totalStudents,\n      tuitionDebt: tuitionDebtCount,\n    };\n    statusCounts.forEach((item: any) => {\n      if (item._id) {\n        let label = item._id;\n        // Normalize legacy labels\n        if (label === \"Đã xong KSK\") label = \"Đã KSK\";\n\n        countsMap[label] = (countsMap[label] || 0) + item.count;\n      }\n    });\n\n    // 11. Unread notification count & recent (Using new NotifyService)\n    const unreadNotificationCount = await notifyService.getUnreadCount(userId);\n    const recentRes = await notifyService.getByUser(userId, { page: 1, limit: 5 });\n    const recentNotifications = recentRes.data;\n\n    log.success(\n      res,\n      {\n        counts: countsMap,\n        totalDebtAmount,\n        monthlyGrowthPercent,\n        thisMonthCount,\n        weeklyExamCount,\n        urgentTasks,\n        unreadNotificationCount,\n        recentNotifications,\n        latestRegistrations,\n        upcomingExams,\n        regionStats,\n        recruiterStats,\n      },\n      \"Dashboard statistics retrieved successfully\",\n    );\n  },\n);\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742309057}}
{"type":"message","id":"61a0d3eb","parentId":"a26bac8b","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:57.646Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the system. Let me also check the exam controller and lesson controller to see the full picture.\n\nCurrent state:\n1. **User model** has roles: `admin`, `staff`, `teacher`, `student`\n2. **UserRole** table links users to roles\n3. **Student controller** already has teacher filtering in `getAllStudents` and `getStudentById`\n4. **Dashboard controller** already has teacher filtering\n5. **Course model** - NO teacher_id field currently\n6. **Lesson model** has `teacher_id` field\n7. **CourseStudent model** (I should check this)\n\nI need to:\n1. Check CourseStudent model to understand the relationship\n2. Check all controllers to see what needs to be updated\n3. Plan the data isolation changes\n\nLet me check more files.","thinkingSignature":"2a3cd9a1b79c564d3db5747f51d9dfa56fa1a3df9a1aa63fac39e57b827d950d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7rtasmkuuoz6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/course_student.model.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7rtasmkuuoz6_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/lesson.controller.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":3374,"output":271,"cacheRead":69461,"cacheWrite":2780,"totalTokens":75886,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776742309069,"responseId":"063622a6eb4e3a0fff9f188db617c2ae"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4459eb67","parentId":"61a0d3eb","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:57.686Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7rtasmkuuoz6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import mongoose, { Schema, Document, Types } from 'mongoose';\n\nexport interface ICourseStudent extends Document {\n  student_id: Types.ObjectId; // References Student(student_infos)\n  course_id: Types.ObjectId; // References Course(course_infos)\n  stadium_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  teacher_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  sale_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  license_category_id?: Types.ObjectId | null;\n  status: 'unfinished' | 'finished' | 'canceled';\n  km: number;\n  hour: string;\n  fee: number;\n  paid_fee: number;\n  balance?: any; // Treasury balance for this enrollment\n  contract_date?: Date | null;\n  status_detail?: string;\n  progress_flags?: {\n    theory_completed: boolean;\n    sand_yard_completed: boolean;\n    simulation_completed: boolean;\n    dat_completed: boolean;\n    cabin_completed: boolean;\n    graduation_eligible: boolean;\n  };\n  health_check?: {\n    status: string;\n    date: Date | null;\n    hospital: string | null;\n    note: string | null;\n  };\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nconst CourseStudentSchema = new Schema<ICourseStudent>({\n  student_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'StudentInfos', required: true, index: true },\n  course_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Courses', required: true, index: true },\n  stadium_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Stadiums', default: null },\n  teacher_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', default: null },\n  sale_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Users', default: null },\n  license_category_id: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'LicenseCategories', default: null },\n  status: { \n    type: String, \n    enum: ['unfinished', 'finished', 'canceled'], \n    default: 'unfinished' \n  },\n  km: { type: Number, default: 0 },\n  hour: { type: String, default: '00:00' },\n  fee: { type: Number, default: 0 },\n  paid_fee: { type: Number, default: 0 },\n  balance: { \n    type: Schema.Types.Decimal128, \n    default: 0,\n    get: (v: any) => (v ? parseFloat(v.toString()) : 0)\n  },\n  contract_date: { type: Date, default: null },\n  status_detail: { type: String, default: 'Chờ KSK' },\n  progress_flags: {\n    theory_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n    sand_yard_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n    simulation_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n    dat_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n    cabin_completed: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n    graduation_eligible: { type: Boolean, default: false },\n  },\n  health_check: {\n    status: { type: String, enum: ['Chờ khám', 'Đủ điều kiện', 'Không đủ điều kiện'], default: 'Chờ khám' },\n    date: { type: Date, default: null },\n    hospital: { type: String, default: null },\n    note: { type: String, default: null },\n  },\n}, {\n  timestamps: { createdAt: 'created_at', updatedAt: 'updated_at' },\n  versionKey: false,\n  collection: 'coursestudents'\n});\n\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ student_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ course_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ status_detail: 1, created_at: -1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ sale_id: 1, created_at: -1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ 'progress_flags.dat_completed': 1, status_detail: 1 });\nCourseStudentSchema.index({ fee: 1, paid_fee: 1 });\n\nexport const CourseStudentModel = mongoose.models.CourseStudents || mongoose.model<ICourseStudent>('CourseStudents', CourseStudentSchema, 'coursestudents');\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742317681}}
{"type":"message","id":"c05934e5","parentId":"4459eb67","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:31:57.693Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7rtasmkuuoz6_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { LessonService } from '@/application/services/lesson.service';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\n\nconst lessonService = new LessonService();\n\nexport const createLesson = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const lesson = await lessonService.createLesson(req.body);\n  res.statusSuccess(lesson, 'Lesson created successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getLessons = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const filter: any = {};\n  if (req.query.category) {\n    filter.category = req.query.category;\n  }\n  if (req.query.status) {\n    filter.status = req.query.status;\n  }\n\n  // Data Isolation for Teachers\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    filter.teacher_id = req.user.id;\n  }\n  \n  const lessons = await lessonService.findLessons(filter, req.pagination);\n  res.statusSuccess(lessons, 'Lessons retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getLessonById = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  \n  // Data Isolation for Teachers\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    const isAssigned = await lessonService.isLessonAssignedToTeacher(idStr, req.user.id);\n    if (!isAssigned) {\n      return res.status(403).json({ success: false, message: 'Bạn không có quyền truy cập buổi học này' });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const lesson = await lessonService.getLessonById(idStr);\n  res.statusSuccess(lesson, 'Lesson retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getByTeacher = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const teacherId = typeof req.params.teacherId === 'string' ? req.params.teacherId : req.params.teacherId[0];\n  const lessons = await lessonService.getLessonsByTeacher(teacherId, req.pagination);\n  res.statusSuccess(lessons, 'Teacher lessons retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getByStudent = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const studentId = typeof req.params.studentId === 'string' ? req.params.studentId : req.params.studentId[0];\n  const lessons = await lessonService.getLessonsByStudent(studentId, req.pagination);\n  res.statusSuccess(lessons, 'Student lessons retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const updateLesson = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n\n  // Data Isolation for Teachers\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    const isAssigned = await lessonService.isLessonAssignedToTeacher(idStr, req.user.id);\n    if (!isAssigned) {\n      return res.status(403).json({ success: false, message: 'Bạn không có quyền cập nhật buổi học này' });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const lesson = await lessonService.updateLesson(idStr, req.body);\n  res.statusSuccess(lesson, 'Lesson updated successfully');\n});\n\nexport const deleteLesson = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n\n  // Data Isolation for Teachers\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    const isAssigned = await lessonService.isLessonAssignedToTeacher(idStr, req.user.id);\n    if (!isAssigned) {\n      return res.status(403).json({ success: false, message: 'Bạn không có quyền xóa buổi học này' });\n    }\n  }\n\n  await lessonService.deleteLesson(idStr);\n  res.statusSuccess(null, 'Lesson deleted successfully');\n});\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742317687}}
{"type":"message","id":"b1a36853","parentId":"c05934e5","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:32:10.870Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me also check exam and payment controllers to complete the picture.","thinkingSignature":"c0d62bc1b2c3793e9ecea408e2b00507355ecc236f6f2942d6ec1a8506ac9b8c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cjt8cg9tdv7y_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/exam.controller.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cjt8cg9tdv7y_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/payment.controller.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1872,"output":111,"cacheRead":72116,"cacheWrite":3708,"totalTokens":77807,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776742317696,"responseId":"063622afb2e85e4fb00238087feec6bb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"88d96700","parentId":"b1a36853","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:32:10.906Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cjt8cg9tdv7y_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type { } from '../types/express.d';\nimport { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { ExamService } from '@/application/services/exam.service';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\n\nconst examService = new ExamService();\n// Controller handles exam routes\n\nexport const getAllExams = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const filters = { ...req.query };\n  if (req.user?.role === 'teacher') {\n    filters.teacher_id = req.user.id;\n  }\n  const exams = await examService.getAllExams(filters, req.pagination);\n  res.statusSuccess(exams, 'Exams retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getExamById = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  const exam = await examService.getExamById(idStr);\n  res.statusSuccess(exam, 'Exam retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const createExam = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const exam = await examService.createExam(req.body);\n  res.statusSuccess(exam, 'Exam created successfully');\n});\n\nexport const updateExam = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  const exam = await examService.updateExam(idStr, req.body);\n  res.statusSuccess(exam, 'Exam updated successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getExamStudents = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : (req.params.id as any)[0];\n  const teacherId = req.user?.role === 'teacher' ? req.user.id : undefined;\n  const students = await examService.getExamStudents(idStr, req.pagination, teacherId);\n  res.statusSuccess(students, 'Exam students retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const deleteExam = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  await examService.deleteExam(idStr);\n  res.statusSuccess(null, 'Exam deleted successfully');\n});\nexport const removeStudentFromExam = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  const studentIdStr = typeof req.params.studentId === 'string' ? req.params.studentId : req.params.studentId[0];\n  await examService.removeStudentFromExam(idStr, studentIdStr);\n  res.statusSuccess(null, 'Student removed from exam successfully');\n});\n\nexport const updateStudentResult = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  const studentIdStr = typeof req.params.studentId === 'string' ? req.params.studentId : req.params.studentId[0];\n  const { result } = req.body;\n  const updatedExam = await examService.updateStudentResult(idStr, studentIdStr, result);\n  res.statusSuccess(updatedExam, 'Student result updated successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getExamsByStudent = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const studentId = typeof req.params.studentId === 'string' ? req.params.studentId : req.params.studentId[0];\n  const exams = await examService.getExamsByStudent(studentId);\n  res.statusSuccess(exams, 'Student exams retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const exportExams = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  await examService.exportExamsToExcel(res, req.query);\n});\n\nexport const getExamStats = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const { type } = req.query;\n  const stats = await examService.getExamStats(type as any);\n  res.statusSuccess(stats, 'Exam statistics retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const importResults = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  if (!req.file) {\n    throw new Error('Please upload a file');\n  }\n  const result = await examService.importResults(idStr, req.file.path);\n  res.statusSuccess(result, 'Results imported successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getResultTemplate = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  await examService.getResultTemplate(res);\n});\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742330900}}
{"type":"message","id":"fee711cc","parentId":"88d96700","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:32:10.913Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cjt8cg9tdv7y_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { PaymentService } from '@/application/services/payment.service';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\nimport { ctrlLogger } from '@/infrastructure/logging/controller-logger';\n\nconst paymentService = new PaymentService();\n// Payment routes\n\nexport const getAllPayments = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.get_all', req);\n  log.start({ query: req.query });\n\n  const payments = await paymentService.getAllPayments(req.query || {}, (req as any).pagination);\n  log.success((res as any), payments, 'Payments retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getPaymentsByStudent = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.get_by_student', req);\n  const studentId = typeof req.params.studentId === 'string' ? req.params.studentId : req.params.studentId[0];\n  log.start({ studentId });\n\n  const payments = await paymentService.getPaymentsByStudent(studentId, (req as any).pagination);\n  log.success((res as any), payments, 'Student payments retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getPaymentStats = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.get_stats', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const stats = await paymentService.getPaymentStats();\n  log.success((res as any), stats, 'Payment stats retrieved successfully');\n});\n\nexport const createPayment = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.create', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  const payment = await paymentService.createPayment(req.body);\n  log.success((res as any), payment, 'Payment recorded successfully');\n});\n\nexport const updatePayment = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.update', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  log.start({ paymentId: idStr });\n\n  const payment = await paymentService.updatePayment(idStr, req.body);\n  log.success((res as any), payment, 'Payment updated successfully');\n});\n\nexport const deletePayment = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.delete', req);\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  log.start({ paymentId: idStr });\n\n  await paymentService.deletePayment(idStr);\n  log.success((res as any), null, 'Payment deleted successfully');\n});\n\nexport const exportPayments = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.export', req);\n  log.start({ query: req.query });\n\n  await paymentService.exportPaymentsToExcel(res, req.query);\n  // Export streams response directly; no success log needed (response already sent)\n});\n\nexport const exportPremiumPayments = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.export_premium', req);\n  log.start({ query: req.query });\n\n  await paymentService.exportPremiumFinancialReport(res, req.query);\n});\n\nexport const importPayments = catchAsync(async (req: any, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.import', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  if (!req.file) {\n    throw new Error('No file uploaded');\n  }\n\n  const result = await paymentService.importPayments(req.file.path, (req as any).user?._id);\n  log.success((res as any), result, 'Payments imported successfully');\n});\n\nexport const getImportTemplate = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const log = ctrlLogger('payment.get_template', req);\n  log.start({});\n\n  await paymentService.getImportTemplate(res);\n});\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776742330907}}
{"type":"message","id":"e427cf90","parentId":"fee711cc","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:32:38.776Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete understanding of the current state. Let me summarize and create a comprehensive plan for resource authorization.\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Already Implemented (Partial):\n1. **Dashboard** - Teacher filtering via `CourseStudentModel.teacher_id`\n2. **Student Controller** - Teacher filtering via `isStudentAssignedToTeacher()` \n3. **Lesson Controller** - Teacher filtering via `teacher_id` field\n4. **Exam Controller** - Teacher filtering via `teacher_id` filter\n\n### NOT Implemented (Needs Work):\n1. **Course Controller** - NO teacher filtering, ALL courses visible\n2. **Payment Controller** - NO teacher filtering, ALL payments visible\n3. **Exam Batch Controller** - Need to check\n4. **Stadium Controller** - Need to check\n5. **Notification Controller** - Need to check\n\n### Key Entities and Relationships:\n- **Course** - No teacher_id field\n- **CourseStudent** - Has `teacher_id`, links Students to Courses\n- **Student** - Has `user_id`, linked via CourseStudent to teacher\n- **Lesson** - Has `teacher_id`, linked directly\n- **Exam** - Has teacher_id filter support\n- **Payment** - No teacher_id field, but should filter by student's teacher\n\n### Authorization Model:\n- `admin` - sees ALL data (no filtering)\n- `teacher` - sees only data where `teacher_id` = their own ID\n- `staff` - needs clarification (same as teacher or admin?)\n- `student` - sees only their own data\n\n### Plan Structure:\n\n1. **Phase 1: Infrastructure**\n   - Create `DataIsolationMiddleware` or `resourceFilter` helper\n   - Define resource-to-owner-field mapping\n   \n2. **Phase 2: Backend Controllers**\n   - Course: Add teacher filtering based on CourseStudent assignments\n   - Payment: Add teacher filtering via CourseStudent relationship\n   - Exam Batch: Add teacher filtering\n   - Stadium: Consider if teachers need stadium-level filtering\n   \n3. **Phase 3: Frontend**\n   - Dashboard adjustments (may already be fine)\n   - Ensure UI doesn't leak data\n\n4. **Phase 4: Testing**\n   - Test admin sees all\n   - Test teacher sees only their students' data\n   - Test other teachers can't see each other's data\n\nNow I should create the detailed plan using the prompt-optimizer agent.","thinkingSignature":"4d8899fb5f87d031793123ee90056520900cd120b7839434abef18004818a6a5"},{"type":"text","text":"Đã đọc xong source code. Bây giờ mình dùng **prompt-optimizer** để cụ thể hóa yêu cầu:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8marazbt1fed_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Context\nYêu cầu từ Khương Nịnh về phân quyền tài nguyên cho dự án AHV QLHV.\n\n## Current System Analysis\n\n### Tech Stack:\n- **Frontend:** Next.js (src/)\n- **Backend:** Node.js/TypeScript (src/)  \n- **Database:** MongoDB\n\n### User Roles (from user.model.ts):\n- `admin` - Admin (xem toàn hệ thống)\n- `teacher` - Giáo viên (chỉ xem dữ liệu của mình)\n- `staff` - Nhân viên\n- `student` - Học viên\n\n### Current Data Isolation Status:\n\n**✅ ĐÃ CÓ (partial):**\n1. `dashboard.controller.ts` - Lọc theo `teacher_id` qua `CourseStudentModel.teacher_id`\n2. `student.controller.ts` - Lọc theo `teacher_id`, kiểm tra `isStudentAssignedToTeacher()`\n3. `lesson.controller.ts` - Lọc theo `teacher_id`\n4. `exam.controller.ts` - Lọc theo `teacher_id`\n\n**❌ CHƯA CÓ (cần làm):**\n1. `course.controller.ts` - KHÔNG lọc theo teacher, thấy TẤT CẢ courses\n2. `payment.controller.ts` - KHÔNG lọc theo teacher, thấy TẤT CẢ payments\n3. `exam_batch.controller.ts` - Cần kiểm tra\n4. `stadium.controller.ts` - Cần kiểm tra\n5. `notification.controller.ts` - Cần kiểm tra\n\n### Key Data Models:\n- `Course` - KHÔNG có teacher_id field\n- `CourseStudent` - Có `teacher_id`, liên kết Students ↔ Courses\n- `Student` - Có `user_id`, liên kết qua CourseStudent\n- `Lesson` - Có `teacher_id`\n- `Payment` - KHÔNG có teacher_id, cần filter qua CourseStudent\n\n## Yêu cầu:\nPhân quyền tài nguyên:\n- **Admin:** Xem toàn hệ thống (không lọc)\n- **Teacher:** Chỉ xem dữ liệu liên quan đến mình qua `teacher_id`\n- **Staff:** Cần xác định (giống admin hay teacher?)\n- **Student:** Chỉ xem dữ liệu của chính mình\n\n## Cần lên kế hoạch chi tiết:\n1. Phân tích các entities cần phân quyền\n2. Xác định owner-field mapping (ai sở hữu data nào)\n3. Thiết kế middleware/helper cho data isolation\n4. Lộ trình implementation từng bước\n5. Frontend considerations\n\nHãy cụ thể hóa yêu cầu này thành SPEC chi tiết để triển khai.","runtime":"subagent","mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1922,"output":1282,"cacheRead":75548,"cacheWrite":2197,"totalTokens":80949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776742330917,"responseId":"063622bc32ebb46ac6a5188450675b4e"}}
